><pubDate>Fri, 04 Aug 2023 15:25:12 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1691162059</ingested><modified> 2023-08-04T15:14:28+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Jon Fingas]]></category><media:content height="3369" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/66e25ab0-32d4-11ee-b5ff-9336ca00cd7e" width="5000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="3369" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/66e25ab0-32d4-11ee-b5ff-9336ca00cd7e" width="5000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ASSOCIATED PRESS]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[A woman poses with a balloon of Pokemon character Pikachu at Minatomirai shopping district in Yokohama, near Tokyo, Monday, Aug. 14, 2017. (AP Photo/Shizuo Kambayashi)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Japan Daily Life]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Johnson & Johnson gets FDA approval for heart treatments that don't require X-rays]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>强生公司的<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.jnjmedtech.com/en-US"><ins>医疗技术部门</ins></a>的<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.jnj.com/biosense-webster-receives-fda-approval-for-multiple-atrial-fibrillation-ablation-products-to-be-used-in-a-workflow-without-fluoroscopy"><ins>新工作流程获得 FDA 批准</ins></a>，该工作流程将使医疗专业人员更安全地治疗心房颤动，心房颤动会导致心跳不规律，并可能<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.mayoclinic.org/diseases-conditions/atrial-fibrillation/symptoms-causes/syc-20350624"><ins>导致中风或心力衰竭</ins></a>。强生 MedTech 旗下 Biosense Webster 开发的多种产品获得了 FDA 的“零透视工作流程”许可，这意味着在导管插入过程中将不再需要实时 X 射线成像。医疗专业人员现在可以使用超声波来指导治疗，而不是使用 X 射线插入 Biosense 导管。</p><p>使用更少的 X 射线或透视检查可以降低患者和医疗专业人员的辐射暴露。目前，在专门治疗相关心脏手术的治疗室工作的医生和医务人员往往会<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://pdf.sciencedirectassets.com/781090/1-s2.0-S2772930323X00052/1-s2.0-S2772930323005318/main.pdf?X-Amz-Security-Token=IQoJb3JpZ2luX2VjEIb%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2FwEaCXVzLWVhc3QtMSJHMEUCIHiy4EcMJSMDfam4qpccciIubvzC5gIZNmQNnyDpNL6zAiEAkcfDkwIKqKNbda8L0DJH%2FqG3hDjwoUjpk7JeyHGUnhYqswUILxAFGgwwNTkwMDM1NDY4NjUiDNOU%2BVJ6fRZGLsdLrCqQBR5ZA%2Fbn%2BIUDPrmikxkj3%2Fcd5ZjfmGsP7isZ0LmWgpGy0UCT728P2fUbPXQqWJ56Ik%2BXK0%2BHXWbLb94jQrbqpkTVSvF8mBKwCQewg37GBbNC8Kj%2BAQnuP62OFdsTsd583HuMqJpOMnT4C3jH7O7%2FstN6tA71mqNslv7XMik9KeR%2BJkp0cYQGikMMngRgg4FqV3QkPLj7PGo9Ifjvh8VkEWT6JJaeRIHtTDbpOZDa37npUp5Sa253oDBzSk9zfsaIFx1QuKnzNKNgl8ZBVVX47aSvXE6ykI44o06g9Yc44KSI1p9ut9bKzRbNtVmmOPjlpYDUOqaxwgT%2Fwt4SYV6LEwxxmJlrim%2BWoICCu2EzhmarCmzTzO4nfH5mmVlSWE5zC7tko5oXhYshQgbb7cnkYbp3aZn7Ob1aIRng80KvbgFLXbSC03no0FQNTQvo2J7ySN9DGR6XJ3pGgbS8dxQqMmhYJOETaSPifGJ2mjbDZ%2B%2FT1iSMXxMe3J%2BjZQAk0zgvhe6aAIeYBGYk5oO9PmnRrGAaReJZJABTNe6Yg5KHUB7%2BWz%2BQCJubH4wEoeWv2MLaFnXDGWJLhjCb4P1hVvWyNF5dUKdJ%2Fo%2FNuwnO0Hoi1a4XTpBO%2B7faSkYVtIJCcaxnLWyubiPILseNRMbRETEDkD28tcBkY1qNzu6%2BoLZQnAKyVy%2B1cc%2Be%2FxRKM9NEitQnOrvVeJ%2BuptIZATk0%2FM4qRLY09jlCojawWztI%2Be5BQjljlSMNNn9uqCcT5Va%2BTNGWjv1z7iEplKX6Yg7sb%2F0yRNFPLAiP1bSvyUbyFcbQ4e2EaN%2Bmw5XuxX7m6ZBHhW0ejvPxhhyWPkS3UeFLvGLbmUEufyM%2Fc4o00sWhPKfNshlaMKGJtKYGOrEBNB0WR4P0SYLmKSGPKZ7s1VL%2FOEyyJMlO78k3x%2Fyg0yHi2%2FESNPxq5tJVr2TdClVc2blfeQQaAx8VpknZqGDqFDoKMswHICuSZl366YoPScrlzGkFxI6DucCxOjTmMiV2S2HJVpJ9dKIz%2FMfZHK0Z6PI1D3uqKxxyUiLGHsBpIc%2B%2FPpon148LCvgCNZptkSEjdy0oCls1KRiWWLgUaqvj1cn5pZKFlw7pQj3ai%2BdUd2q7&amp;X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256&amp;X-Amz-Date=20230804T144044Z&amp;X-Amz-SignedHeaders=host&amp;X-Amz-Expires=300&amp;X-Amz-Credential=ASIAQ3PHCVTY4IVGBJ5M%2F20230804%2Fus-east-1%2Fs3%2Faws4_request&amp;X-Amz-Signature=77ff6e0c8efadfdba89c200ca286ee187007f330d505e50b58e9cbde641de98a&amp;hash=ea27866b0b8c91145d8a73a1b1309d63d7668a2290b7bd8addc1505eb7df11f6&amp;host=68042c943591013ac2b2430a89b270f6af2c76d8dfd086a07176afe7c76c2c61&amp;pii=S2772930323005318&amp;tid=spdf-9fae0e27-f30f-4e1c-9a51-dff8e19cdb4b&amp;sid=89948b2d9ba26046ee398e713b63c799d837gxrqa&amp;type=client&amp;tsoh=d3d3LnNjaWVuY2VkaXJlY3QuY29t&amp;ua=0f12550653545f000257&amp;rr=7f178ea808ca8e02&amp;cc=us">随着时间的推移受到过多的辐射</a>，这可能会导致眼睛问题、癌症和骨损伤等问题。 FDA 的批准有助于解决反复出现的职业危害。在应用新批准的工作流程时，在导管实验室工作的提供者也不必再穿戴铅围裙等重型防护装备，从而降低了长期肌肉和骨骼疼痛的风险。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> FDA 的这一举措标志着同类产品中的第一个也是唯一一个批准。竖起大拇指是基于 REAL AF 登记处（或电生理学领域的真实世界证据登记处）的临床试验和研究数据。数据支持了治疗在现实生活中的效果。新方法仅适用于 Biosense 产品，例如最常用的消融导管<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.jnjmedtech.com/en-US/product/thermocool-smarttouch-sf-catheter"><ins>THERMOCOOL SMARTTOUCH SF 导管</ins></a>等。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/johnson--johnson-gets-fda-approval-for-heart-treatments-that-dont-require-x-rays-150913343.html?src= RSS]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/johnson--johnson-gets-fda-approval-for-heart-treatments-that-dont-require-x-rays-150913343.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 4fd1be02-adb5-4bf1-b49e-835831735ecd</guid><dc:creator>马拉克·萨利赫</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 04 Aug 2023 15:09:13 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1691161754</ingested><modified> 2023-08-04T15:09:17+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Health Care Industry]]></category><category><![CDATA[Health]]></category><category><![CDATA[Tests & Procedures]]></category><category><![CDATA[Disease & Medical Conditions]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Malak Saleh]]></category><media:content height="3024" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/99b067e0-32d2-11ee-bfd7-c368a0d30d0b" width="4032"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="3280" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/8a5596d0-32d2-11ee-b70a-197f964f4bc1" width="4928"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Universal Images Group via Getty]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Reportage in the Interventional Cardiology and Rythmology service in Saint George Clinic in Nice, France. Radiofrequency ablation of cardiac arrhythmia using the Stereotaxis robotic system. This operation consists of inserting a catheter into the heart, emitting radio waves that will cauterize cardiac tissue responsible for rhythmic irregularity. The Stereotaxis robotic system is a magnetic navigation system. It uses a rotating magnetic field enabling the ablation catheter to be guided from a distance. The system consists of two giant magnets placed on each side of the operating table. The operation is carried out under radioscopic control. It is a more precise technique that reduces the risk of complications, procedure length and the patient’s and radiologist’s exposure time to x-rays. Treating a patient suffering from a left atrial flutter. Before the ablation, electrophysiological analyses are carried out, as well as a 3D map of the heart in order to precisely locate the areas in the heart responsible for arrhythmia.
The doctor uses a catheter for mapping and electrophysiological cardiac monitoring.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Radiofrequency Ablation]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The best live TV streaming services in 2023]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>流媒体向我们承诺了一个没有有线电视合同的世界，以及只为我们<em>真正</em>想观看的内容付费的满足感。但代价是什么？切断电源可能意味着您无法观看本地频道、体育直播或某些“仅限有线”网络。如果您想在不签订合同的情况下获得有线电视所提供的一些服务，那么直播电视流媒体服务可能就是您所需要的。我们测试了六种最受欢迎​​的产品，比较了每种产品的功能、价格和可用性，为不同类型的电视爱好者提供了最佳的直播电视流媒体服务。</p><h2>在直播电视流媒体服务中寻找什么</h2><h3><strong>如何直播电视节目</strong></h3><p>流媒体直播电视很像使用 Netflix。您可以通过手机、平板电脑、智能电视、 <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-streaming-devices-media-players-123021395.html">流媒体设备</a>或 xBox 或 Playstation 等游戏系统上的应用程序进行访问，并且信号通过互联网到达。更快、更稳定的互联网连接往往会给您带来更好的体验。大多数直播电视应用程序要求您通过网络浏览器注册并付款。之后，您可以在设备上激活该应用程序。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><h3><strong>价格</strong></h3><p>当我开始研究时，我对直播电视和 Netflix 或 Peacock 等<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-video-streaming-services-133000093.html">标准流媒体应用程序</a>之间的价格差异感到震惊。后者的费用在每月 5 至 20 美元之间，而许多直播电视服务的价格约为 70 美元，如果加上额外的福利、频道套餐和额外费用，价格可能会高于 100 美元。我还了解到，就基本计划而言，较高的价格标签主要是由于提供多个网络的成本 - 特别是体育和本地电台。</p><h3><strong>本地频道</strong></h3><p>我们尝试过的服务中只有两项不包括完整的本地频道覆盖，其中一项不努力播放体育节目。那就是 Philo，正如你可能猜到的那样，它是最便宜的。下一个最实惠的选择是 Sling，仅在较大的市场上覆盖三个本地电视台，但它仍然设法包含一些顶级体育频道。</p><p>当您向任何处理本地电视的提供商注册时，您将输入您的邮政编码，以确保您获得您所在地区的 ABC、CBS、FOX 和 NBC 的广播附属公司。当然，您也可以免费获得这些电台。几乎所有现代电视机都支持射频 (RF) 连接，也称为同轴端口，这意味着如果您购买<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAdNjSFySHUB5LvTxXF-PeO0y_Q2BikkE25wwz5DoNvP8&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FTV-Antenna-Indoor-Booster-Signal%2Fdp%2FB0BF9M8DVH">高清天线</a>，您将收到 ABC、CBS、FOX 和 NBC 等本地广播电台。由于信号是数字信号，因此接收效果比静态的兔耳时代有了很大改善。</p><h3><strong>运动的</strong></h3><p>令我头晕的一个现实是现有体育网络的数量之多和迭代程度。试图找出哪个网络将承载您想要查看的比赛可能会很棘手。谷歌通过列出<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Google;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=0931b986-736e-47bb-80b9-5f6f8f4ef5ae&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Google&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiIwOTMxYjk4Ni03MzZlLTQ3YmItODBiOS01ZjZmOGY0ZWY1YWUiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZ29vZ2xlLmNvbS9zZWFyY2g_cT11cGNvbWluZytuYmErZ2FtZXMiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjUwZWIzNGRiLWMwZmMtNGJmYi1hYjQxLTFjYmU5N2ZhZmZkOCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAesTVaWGoJAGC8HeWPR-hONFNNDQi_RYK1Xsn7p9P7eQ&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Fsearch%3Fq%3Dupcoming%2Bnba%2Bgames">即将举行的比赛</a>，让体育迷的生活变得更容易：如果你点击一场比赛，“电视和流媒体”按钮会告诉你哪个网络正在报道该赛事。</p><p>只需要弄清楚您选择的服务是否承载该区域体育网络即可。不幸的是，即使有附加组件和额外的套餐，一些提供商也根本没有特定的频道阵容。需要律师才能了解<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/south-park-warner-bros-discovery-paramount-lawsuit-211615299.html">流媒体版权谈判</a>的来龙去脉，而且电视网络始终会离开并返回直播电视运营商。也就是说，美国大多数主要体育赛事均由 ESPN、福克斯体育、TNT、USA 和当地附属机构报道。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-03/3cbec0e0-c42d-11ed-bfbe-961d0e86297a" alt="显示 Philo、Sling、Hulu、DirecTV Stream、fuboTV 和 YouTube TV 应用徽标的电视。" data-uuid="745efd02-508c-3603-a480-547937b3d664"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">艾米·斯科海姆 / Engadget</div></figure><h3><strong>传统有线网络</strong></h3><p>数十个网络曾经只能通过有线电视观看，例如 Bravo、BET、Food Network、HGTV、CNN、Lifetime、SYFY 和 MTV。如果您只订阅 Max 和 Netflix，您将无法访问其中任何一个。我们测试的所有选项都提供了大量的有线网络列表，但只有 DirecTV 为您提供了<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://sports.yahoo.com/126-cable-channels-ranked-2022-183059118.html">尼尔森</a>2022 年收视率最高的 36 个频道的全部内容。</p><p>媒体集团不断<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/warnermedia-discovery-merger-hbo-max-discovery-plus-214335645.html">合并</a>、 <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/epix-relaunch-mgm-plus-140538789.html">重塑品牌</a>或重新进入流媒体市场，这意味着您可以在 Peacock 等传统视频流媒体服务上找到许多有线网络。 AMC+ 等其他频道都有自己的独立应用程序。 If you&#39;re just interested in live TV for cable-only shows, there are cheaper alternatives. I was particularly delighted by the 20 ad-free channels you get on the <a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Discovery+;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=e3296106-c693-4525-ba0e-6b65767ea99e&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Discovery%2B&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiJlMzI5NjEwNi1jNjkzLTQ1MjUtYmEwZS02YjY1NzY3ZWE5OWUiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZGlzY292ZXJ5cGx1cy5jb20vIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI1MGViMzRkYi1jMGZjLTRiZmItYWI0MS0xY2JlOTdmYWZmZDgifQ&amp;signature=AQAAATxGz2ytnj6015YElXRvBTyedZd22GCfa43yqWiVYBRl&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.discoveryplus.com%2F">Discovery+</a> app for $7 per month. In addition to original content, Paramount+ has shows from multiple brands like MTV and Comedy Central, while Peacock has Bravo and Hallmark shows.</p><p> There&#39;s even a service called <a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3RyeS5mcm5kbHl0di5jb20vIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI1MGViMzRkYi1jMGZjLTRiZmItYWI0MS0xY2JlOTdmYWZmZDgifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAVsZIkFL_NAsojioaxhFb7VBEX8KUhX8w_0zsJABNpm3&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Ftry.frndlytv.com%2F">Frndly TV</a> that costs a mere $7 per month and streams A&amp;E, Lifetime, Game Show Network, Vice and about 35 others. We didn&#39;t test it for this guide because it doesn&#39;t give you local access, news or sports and most people would be better served by the broader coverage on a cheap option like Philo.</p><p> I should also mention free ad-supported TV ( <a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/youtube-is-testing-a-hub-of-free-cable-style-channels-192518784.html">FAST</a> ) streamers like <a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1" href="https://www.plex.tv/">Plex</a> , <a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1" href="https://tubitv.com/">Tubi</a> , <a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1" href="https://pluto.tv/welcome">PlutoTV</a> and <a data-i13n="cpos:15;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Sling TV;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=34c77505-6db4-4664-9320-2c38b4122d5e&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Sling+TV&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiIzNGM3NzUwNS02ZGI0LTQ2NjQtOTMyMC0yYzM4YjQxMjJkNWUiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2xpbmcuY29tL2ZyZWVzdHJlYW0iLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjUwZWIzNGRiLWMwZmMtNGJmYi1hYjQxLTFjYmU5N2ZhZmZkOCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAcyvv1f4WLcVCmGT-rEGdv_2DOP0m5Yn54fVrXNGM8D4&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sling.com%2Ffreestream">Sling Freestream</a> that let you drop in and watch a decent selection of live networks at zero cost. Some don&#39;t even require a credit card. And if you have a Roku device or a Samsung TV, you can access hundreds of live channels via the <a data-i13n="cpos:16;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Roku;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=f3574a52-3bcf-4a37-83ee-65836ac78115&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Roku&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiJmMzU3NGE1Mi0zYmNmLTRhMzctODNlZS02NTgzNmFjNzgxMTUiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cucm9rdS5jb20vYmxvZy9saXZlLXR2LWNoYW5uZWwtZ3VpZGUiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjUwZWIzNGRiLWMwZmMtNGJmYi1hYjQxLTFjYmU5N2ZhZmZkOCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAASZfBxDz8Gv_hwIxJckRhMKzdWdnKp1y962ni-NMZTa9&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.roku.com%2Fblog%2Flive-tv-channel-guide">Roku Channel</a> or through the <a data-i13n="cpos:17;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Samsung Electronics;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=f85e63cd-e13c-4f9d-991c-9fbaadede3ac&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Samsung+Electronics&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiJmODVlNjNjZC1lMTNjLTRmOWQtOTkxYy05ZmJhYWRlZGUzYWMiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2Ftc3VuZy5jb20vdXMvdGVsZXZpc2lvbnMtaG9tZS10aGVhdGVyL3R2cy90dnBsdXMvIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI1MGViMzRkYi1jMGZjLTRiZmItYWI0MS0xY2JlOTdmYWZmZDgifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAdyIex31lMvycVVdw9tCy4RN348RUa9MCVRBRdvYCokU&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.samsung.com%2Fus%2Ftelevisions-home-theater%2Ftvs%2Ftvplus%2F">Samsung TV Plus</a> app.</p><h3> How to stream live TV for free</h3><p> I should also mention free ad-supported TV ( <a data-i13n="cpos:18;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/youtube-is-testing-a-hub-of-free-cable-style-channels-192518784.html">FAST</a> ) streamers like <a data-i13n="cpos:19;pos:1" href="https://www.plex.tv/">Plex</a> , <a data-i13n="cpos:20;pos:1" href="https://tubitv.com/">Tubi</a> , <a data-i13n="cpos:21;pos:1" href="https://pluto.tv/welcome">PlutoTV</a> and <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Sling TV;elmt:;cpos:22;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=34c77505-6db4-4664-9320-2c38b4122d5e&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Sling+TV&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiIzNGM3NzUwNS02ZGI0LTQ2NjQtOTMyMC0yYzM4YjQxMjJkNWUiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2xpbmcuY29tL2ZyZWVzdHJlYW0iLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjUwZWIzNGRiLWMwZmMtNGJmYi1hYjQxLTFjYmU5N2ZhZmZkOCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAcyvv1f4WLcVCmGT-rEGdv_2DOP0m5Yn54fVrXNGM8D4&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sling.com%2Ffreestream" class="rapid-with-clickid">Sling Freestream</a> that let you drop in and watch a decent selection of live networks at zero cost. Some don&#39;t even require a credit card. And if you have a Roku device or a Samsung TV, you can access hundreds of live channels via the <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Roku;elmt:;cpos:23;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=f3574a52-3bcf-4a37-83ee-65836ac78115&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Roku&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiJmMzU3NGE1Mi0zYmNmLTRhMzctODNlZS02NTgzNmFjNzgxMTUiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cucm9rdS5jb20vd2hhdHMtb24vdGhlLXJva3UtY2hhbm5lbCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiNTBlYjM0ZGItYzBmYy00YmZiLWFiNDEtMWNiZTk3ZmFmZmQ4In0&amp;signature=AQAAAfDZRcYwvG_GMXdrcN4g81OSpEVDGyEZwt6FCcRnPFTQ&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.roku.com%2Fwhats-on%2Fthe-roku-channel" class="rapid-with-clickid">Roku Channel</a> or through the <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Samsung Electronics;elmt:;cpos:24;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=f85e63cd-e13c-4f9d-991c-9fbaadede3ac&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Samsung+Electronics&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiJmODVlNjNjZC1lMTNjLTRmOWQtOTkxYy05ZmJhYWRlZGUzYWMiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2Ftc3VuZy5jb20vdXMvdGVsZXZpc2lvbnMtaG9tZS10aGVhdGVyL3R2cy90dnBsdXMvIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI1MGViMzRkYi1jMGZjLTRiZmItYWI0MS0xY2JlOTdmYWZmZDgifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAdyIex31lMvycVVdw9tCy4RN348RUa9MCVRBRdvYCokU&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.samsung.com%2Fus%2Ftelevisions-home-theater%2Ftvs%2Ftvplus%2F" class="rapid-with-clickid">Samsung TV Plus</a> app.</p><h3> <strong>Digital video recordings (DVR)</strong></h3><p> Every option we&#39;ve included offers cloud DVR storage, so you don&#39;t need a separate physical device like you often do with traditional cable. You&#39;ll either get unlimited storage for recordings that expires after nine months or a year, or you&#39;ll get a set number of hours (between 50 and 1,000) that you can keep indefinitely. Typically, all you need to do is designate what you want to record and the DVR component will do all the hard work of saving subsequent episodes for you to watch later.</p><p> Aside from being able to watch whenever it&#39;s most convenient, you can also fast-forward through commercials in recorded content. In contrast, you can&#39;t skip them on live TV or video-on-demand (VOD).</p><p> Most live TV subscriptions include access to a selection of VOD content including movies and shows that are currently airing on your subscribed networks. This typically doesn&#39;t cover live events, local shows and news programming. But it does let you watch specific episodes of ongoing shows like <em>Diners, Drive-Ins and Dives</em> or BET&#39;s <em>Sistas</em> . Just search the on-demand library for the program, pick an episode and hit play.</p><h3> <strong>Tiers, packages and add-ons</strong></h3><p> Comparing price-to-offering ratios is a task for a spreadsheet. I… made three. The base plans range from $25 to $75 per month. From there, you can add on packages, which are usually groups of live TV channels bundled by themes like news, sports, entertainment or international. Those cost an extra $5 to $20 per month and simply show up in the guide where you find the rest of your base-level live TV.</p><p> Then there are more premium VOD add-ons, such as Max, AMC+, Starz or Showtime. You may already have these through standalone apps. If you don&#39;t, or if you prefer a combined bill and one access point for your streaming, many live TV subscriptions let you add them.</p><h2> How we tested</h2><p> When I begin testing for a guide, I research the most popular and well-reviewed players in the category and narrow down which are worth trying. For this space, just six services dominate, so I tried them all. After getting them set up using my laptop, I downloaded the apps on a Samsung smart TV running the latest version of Tizen OS. I counted the local stations and regional sports coverage, and noted how many of last year&#39;s <a data-i13n="cpos:25;pos:1" href="https://sports.yahoo.com/126-cable-channels-ranked-2022-183059118.html">top cable networks</a> were available. I then weighed the prices, base packages and available add-ons.</p><p> I then looked at how the programming was organized in each app&#39;s UI and judged how easy everything was to navigate, from the top navigation to the settings. To test the search function, I searched for the same few TV shows on BET, Food Network, HGTV and Comedy Central, since all six providers carry those channels. I noted how helpful the searches were and how quickly they got me to season 6, episode 13 of <em>Home Town</em> .</p><p> I used DVR to record entire series and single movies and watched VOD shows, making sure to test the pause and scan functions. On each service with sports, I searched for the same four upcoming NHL, NBA, MLS and NCAA basketball matches and used the record option to save the games and play them back a day or two later. Finally, I noted any extra perks or irritating quirks.</p><p> Here&#39;s the full list of everything we tried:</p><ul><li><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:26;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Philo;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=b250d7a0-0e4e-4332-bc87-bf6e669b0564&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Philo&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiJiMjUwZDdhMC0wZTRlLTQzMzItYmM4Ny1iZjZlNjY5YjA1NjQiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cucGhpbG8uY29tL2xvZ2luL3N1YnNjcmliZSIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiNTBlYjM0ZGItYzBmYy00YmZiLWFiNDEtMWNiZTk3ZmFmZmQ4In0&amp;signature=AQAAAabIVZR19dFPFnrkXwC-HZhqdthhzjQEXtk-uUzjcKrv&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.philo.com%2Flogin%2Fsubscribe">Philo</a></p></li><li><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:27;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Sling TV;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=34c77505-6db4-4664-9320-2c38b4122d5e&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Sling+TV&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiIzNGM3NzUwNS02ZGI0LTQ2NjQtOTMyMC0yYzM4YjQxMjJkNWUiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2xpbmcuY29tLyIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiNTBlYjM0ZGItYzBmYy00YmZiLWFiNDEtMWNiZTk3ZmFmZmQ4In0&amp;signature=AQAAAQuX1x-8Li1Y3BleLw5tlSNrUlv0th9PPvhRuDrLsSQD&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sling.com%2F">Sling</a></p></li><li><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:28;pos:1" href="https://tv.youtube.com/welcome/">YouTube TV</a></p></li><li><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:29;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Hulu;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=ca19dea0-e7ad-4f54-beed-6302bce56589&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Hulu&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiJjYTE5ZGVhMC1lN2FkLTRmNTQtYmVlZC02MzAyYmNlNTY1ODkiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuaHVsdS5jb20vbGl2ZS10diIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiNTBlYjM0ZGItYzBmYy00YmZiLWFiNDEtMWNiZTk3ZmFmZmQ4In0&amp;signature=AQAAASOsz4gSX7PSfobz14RykoXuU9OPnxuKEPPXAKT0mdHs&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hulu.com%2Flive-tv">Hulu + Live TV</a></p></li><li><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:30;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:DIRECTV;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=fd7207b2-1b6a-4385-aa15-2f04784de078&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=DIRECTV&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiJmZDcyMDdiMi0xYjZhLTQzODUtYWExNS0yZjA0Nzg0ZGUwNzgiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZGlyZWN0di5jb20vc3RyZWFtLyIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiNTBlYjM0ZGItYzBmYy00YmZiLWFiNDEtMWNiZTk3ZmFmZmQ4In0&amp;signature=AQAAAZCwHkjcdTHbgJbx0h8bZZ50xk2YCKyUPzrRoo-1iCLq&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.directv.com%2Fstream%2F">DirecTV Stream</a></p></li><li><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:31;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:FuboTV;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=9a941868-c063-4b44-9207-896f1fb5891e&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=FuboTV&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI5YTk0MTg2OC1jMDYzLTRiNDQtOTIwNy04OTZmMWZiNTg5MWUiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cDovL3d3dy5mdWJvLnR2L3dlbGNvbWU_aXJhZD0zNDM3NDcmaXJtcD0yNTM2MjE3JnBhcnRuZXJwcm9wZXJ0eWlkPTMxNDI4MjMmc3ViSWQzPXhpZDpmcjE2NzQyNTQ5ODIwMDhiaGIiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6IjUwZWIzNGRiLWMwZmMtNGJmYi1hYjQxLTFjYmU5N2ZhZmZkOCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAbfV5QVpXnp6Zv4vvSRE-0I6_ukuICBOH21I_DjeUyw3&amp;gcReferrer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.fubo.tv%2Fwelcome%3Firad%3D343747%26irmp%3D2536217%26partnerpropertyid%3D3142823%26subId3%3Dxid%3Afr1674254982008bhb">FuboTV</a></p></li></ul><h2> Most well-rounded: YouTube TV </h2><p><core-commerce id="5782c9e2123646cc8118d90a96ffb055" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> Google&#39;s option makes a strong case for delivering the best streaming service for live TV. Compared to our top pick for sports, <a data-i13n="cpos:32;pos:1" href="https://tv.youtube.com/welcome/">YouTube TV</a> covers major and minor teams, regional games and national matchups almost as well. It gives you clear navigation, a great search function, unlimited DVR and broad network coverage. It&#39;s not quite as affordable as it once was, as YouTube recently <a data-i13n="cpos:33;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/youtube-tv-raises-prices-to-an-outrageous-73-per-month-182517379.html">raised the price</a> to $73 per month – and it&#39;s even more financially precarious if you&#39;re not great at resisting temptation.</p><p> Upon signup, you&#39;re presented with nearly 50 different add-ons, including 4K resolution, premium channels and themed packages. Even if you fight the urge to roll Max, Shudder and AcornTV into the mix at signup, the enticement remains as it&#39;s dangerously easy to add more to your subscription. If you search for a program on a network you don&#39;t have, you&#39;re prompted to add it. And of course, you can also rent or buy movies that aren&#39;t currently showing on any channels, just like you can via YouTube. While it&#39;s convenient to be able to order up anything you might want on a whim, I imagine this pushes many users&#39; bills far above Google&#39;s listed $73 per month.</p><p> Still, it&#39;s nice to have all your entertainment in one place. And if you <em>only</em> want the add-ons, you can actually subscribe to most of the standalone networks without paying for the base plan. Either way, you get a familiar user experience, with navigation you&#39;ll recognize if you&#39;ve spent any time on regular ol&#39; YouTube. Unsurprisingly, Google&#39;s search function was the best of the bunch, finding the shows and games I searched for quickly and giving me clear choices for how to watch and record.</p><p> At signup, you&#39;ll also pick the shows, networks and teams you like, which are added to your library. YouTube TV then automatically records them. You get unlimited cloud DVR space (though recordings expire after nine months) and it&#39;s dead simple to add programming to your library. Like a real cable experience, YouTube TV autoplays your last-watched program upon startup by default, but it was the only service that allowed me to turn that feature off by heading to the settings.</p><p> Searching for and recording an upcoming game was easy. Once the game was recorded, I had to hunt a little to find it in my library (turns out single games are listed under the Events heading, not Sports). But after that, playback was simple and included a fascinating extra feature: You can either play a recorded game from the beginning or hit Watch Key Plays. The latter gives you between 12 and 20 highlight snippets, each about 10 seconds long. It focuses on the most impressive shots in an NBA bout and includes every goal in an MLS matchup. The feature was available for NCAA basketball and in-season major American leagues (hockey, soccer and basketball at the time of testing). Foreign and more minor games didn&#39;t have the feature.</p><p> Sports fans will also appreciate the new multiview feature that YouTube TV added earlier this year that lets you pick up to four sports, news and weather channels from a select list and view them all at the same time on your screen. If you find yourself constantly flipping back and forth between games, this could save you some hassle.</p><p> YouTube TV also gives you the most in-app settings. You can add parental controls to a profile or pull up a stats menu that shows your buffer health and connection speeds. You can lower playback resolution for slow connections and even send feedback to YouTube. It was also the best at integrating VOD and live programming. For example, if you search for a show that happens to be playing live, a red badge in the corner of the show&#39;s image lets you know it&#39;s on right now. Other services didn&#39;t display this info as clearly.</p><p> Now that YouTube TV is $73 per month, it&#39;s no longer cheaper than <a data-i13n="cpos:34;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Hulu;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=ca19dea0-e7ad-4f54-beed-6302bce56589&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Hulu&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiJjYTE5ZGVhMC1lN2FkLTRmNTQtYmVlZC02MzAyYmNlNTY1ODkiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuaHVsdS5jb20vbGl2ZS10diIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiNTBlYjM0ZGItYzBmYy00YmZiLWFiNDEtMWNiZTk3ZmFmZmQ4In0&amp;signature=AQAAASOsz4gSX7PSfobz14RykoXuU9OPnxuKEPPXAKT0mdHs&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hulu.com%2Flive-tv">Hulu + Live TV</a> , which is $70. And if you already subscribe to the regular Hulu app, this is definitely the better better choice. Hulu&#39;s option gives you live TV streaming, plus all of Hulu&#39;s content, some of which you can&#39;t get elsewhere.</p><p> Hulu + Live TV carries your local affiliates and 32 of the top 36 cable channels, which is the same number as YouTube TV. For sports, you get all available ESPN iterations plus FS1, FS2, TBS, USA, TNT, NBC Golf and the NFL Network. You can also add on premium VOD channels like Max and Showtime, and it&#39;s the only provider that includes Disney+ at no extra cost.</p><p> Navigation on Hulu + Live TV isn&#39;t as smooth as most of the other options – it felt like the live component had been shoehorned into the standard Hulu app. But if you&#39;re already comfortable with (and paying for) Hulu, upgrading to the live TV bundle might be worthwhile.</p><p> <strong>YouTube TV</strong></p><ul><li><p> Base plan: $73/mo</p></li><li><p> Local channels: Yes</p></li><li><p> Top cable channels: 32 of 36</p></li><li><p> DVR limits: Unlimited, 9-month expiration</p></li><li><p> Profiles per account: 6</p></li><li><p> Simultaneous at-home streams: 3 (unlimited with upgrade)</p></li><li><p> Picture in picture mode: Yes</p></li></ul><p> <strong>Hulu + Live TV</strong></p><ul><li><p> Base plan: $70/mo</p></li><li><p> Local channels: Yes</p></li><li><p> Top cable channels: 32 of 36</p></li><li><p> DVR limits: Unlimited, 9-month expiration</p></li><li><p> Profiles per account: 6</p></li><li><p> Simultaneous at-home streams: 2 (unlimited with upgrade)</p></li><li><p> Picture in picture mode: No</p></li></ul><h2> Best cable without a contract: DirecTV Stream </h2><p><core-commerce id="098b5d0272e54a0db7837a7ed79bc0b5" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> Canceling cable is <a data-i13n="cpos:35;pos:1" href="https://www.reddit.com/r/brooklynninenine/comments/cgt6nq/i_need_you_to_cancel_my_cable/">no joke</a> – those contracts are <em>binding</em> . But if you enjoy the serendipity of flipping from one channel to the next and having access to as many networks as possible, <a data-i13n="cpos:36;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3N0cmVhbXR2LmRpcmVjdHYuY29tLyIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiNTBlYjM0ZGItYzBmYy00YmZiLWFiNDEtMWNiZTk3ZmFmZmQ4In0&amp;signature=AQAAAdcf5W3Vm5-FJv1zdJ3KP6SN7FzIWHiSqW07po7lGxqU&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fstreamtv.directv.com%2F">DirecTV Stream</a> will give you a very similar experience to cable without shackling you to a contract. Like cable, it allows you to jump to the “next” sequential channel (yes, DirecTV Stream numbers its channels) with a single button press, transforming the left and right d-pad buttons of a smart TV remote into the rocker on a standard clicker.</p><p> It carries all the top 36 cable networks (though Game Show Network and Animal Planet are only available at the second tier and above) and lets you add multiple packages and premiums like Showtime, Starz, AMC+ and Discovery+. You can also add Max, just like on YouTube TV and Hulu + Live TV, but DirecTV is the only one we tried that lets you add Peacock. Of course, you can always add those apps separately to your smart TV, but for anyone who prefers the all-in-one convenience of cable, it&#39;s a nice perk.</p><p> When you fire up DirecTV Stream, whichever network you last watched automatically starts playing. It continues when you switch over to the guide or other menu pages. If you&#39;re used to the quieter experience of traditional streaming apps (after you turn off <a data-i13n="cpos:37;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2020-02-06-netflix-autoplay-preview-settings.html">autoplay</a> ), you might find that a little distracting.</p><p> The navigation didn&#39;t feel intuitive, partly because the menu options overlay the currently playing show and because there are so many ways to browse, access and control live, recorded and on-demand content. The search function was the least integrated of the services I tested. Instead of live-suggesting as you type, it forces you to enter your full search term on a separate keyboard interface. Even with that limitation, it found the shows and movies I searched for and accurately presented the upcoming games I wanted just from typing in one of the teams.</p><p> You can&#39;t add new channels or packages through the app, which might be a relief to anyone worried about succumbing to subscription overload. Everyone else may just find it annoying.</p><ul><li><p> Base plan: $75/mo</p></li><li><p> Local channels: Yes</p></li><li><p> Top cable channels: 36 of 36</p></li><li><p> DVR limits: Unlimited, 9-month expiration (maximum of 30 episodes per series)</p></li><li><p> Profiles per account: 1</p></li><li><p> Simultaneous at-home streams: Unlimited</p></li><li><p> Picture in picture mode: No</p></li></ul><h2> Best for live sports: FuboTV </h2><p><core-commerce id="c1c7aed949a941bf8836667bc394688b" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> If you want to stream live sports, you should probably opt for <a data-i13n="cpos:38;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=9a941868-c063-4b44-9207-896f1fb5891e&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=FuboTV&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI5YTk0MTg2OC1jMDYzLTRiNDQtOTIwNy04OTZmMWZiNTg5MWUiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZnViby50di93ZWxjb21lIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI1MGViMzRkYi1jMGZjLTRiZmItYWI0MS0xY2JlOTdmYWZmZDgifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAd2jf7G-Y7GYxiqagnhDJbE-y7bjBQ2o8NrishZ2kMs7&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fubo.tv%2Fwelcome&amp;uuid=GAOsSarwKnnvMLLt30704">FuboTV</a> . When you first sign up, it asks which teams you follow across all kinds of associations. Pick teams from in-season leagues and you&#39;ll quickly have DVR content to watch. That&#39;s because Fubo records every game your chosen teams play as long as it&#39;s aired on a supported channel – and its sports coverage is vast.</p><p> I tested out a premium subscription and the guide said there were 118 sports networks to choose from. In addition to the usual suspects from ESPN, Fox, NBC and CBS, you can watch motorsports, international leagues, adventure sports and even poker. Add-ons give you NBA TV, NHL Network, NFL Red Zone and MLB Network. And if you need access to all one thousand games the NBA plays in a season, you can add the NBA League Pass to your lineup for $15 per month. FuboTV even has its <em>own</em> sports channels.</p><p> Yes, the coverage is comprehensive, but FuboTV also made finding and recording specific games very easy. Searching for an upcoming game was simple, as was sifting through the ample amount of recorded games I ended up with. I particularly liked FanView for live games, which inserts the video into a smaller window and surrounds that window with continually updating stats plus a clickable list of other games currently airing.</p><p> FuboTV has made an obvious effort to win at sports, but recently it&#39;s tried to deliver on the live TV experience as well. Based on what I&#39;ve seen so far, it&#39;s certainly made strides. The guide was impressive in the number of ways it let you organize live TV, yet everything felt clean and uncluttered. The Home, Sports, Shows and Movies pages were filled with recommendations and many iterations of categories, with almost all suggestions being live TV.</p><p> Where FuboTV falls short is in VOD access and DVR playback. It wasn&#39;t the best at finding the shows I searched for, and navigating available VOD content wasn&#39;t as breezy as browsing through live programming. The lack of a pop-up preview window as you fast forward or rewind through recordings makes it tough to gauge where you are in a show. As for price, FuboTV ties with DirecTV Stream for the most expensive base package at $75. But if you need <em>all</em> the sports – and want some nicely organized live TV during the few moments when there&#39;s not a game on – this is the way to go.</p><ul><li><p> Base plan: $75/mo</p></li><li><p> Local channels: Yes</p></li><li><p> Top cable channels: 29 of 36</p></li><li><p> DVR limits: 1000 hours, no expiration</p></li><li><p> Profiles per account: 6</p></li><li><p> Simultaneous at-home streams: 10</p></li><li><p> Picture in picture mode: Yes (Apple TV only)</p></li></ul><h2> Most customizable: Sling TV </h2><p><core-commerce id="735b4ade5df448b598929743f894ed90" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> To me, the idea of spending time fine-tuning channel choices sounds exhausting. But if you&#39;re the type who wants to get exactly what you want without paying for too much of what you don&#39;t, <a data-i13n="cpos:39;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Sling TV;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=34c77505-6db4-4664-9320-2c38b4122d5e&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Sling+TV&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiIzNGM3NzUwNS02ZGI0LTQ2NjQtOTMyMC0yYzM4YjQxMjJkNWUiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2xpbmcuY29tLyIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiNTBlYjM0ZGItYzBmYy00YmZiLWFiNDEtMWNiZTk3ZmFmZmQ4In0&amp;signature=AQAAAQuX1x-8Li1Y3BleLw5tlSNrUlv0th9PPvhRuDrLsSQD&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sling.com%2F">Sling TV</a> may be your best bet. It breaks its base plan into two packages, Blue and Orange, with different channels on each. Blue, which costs $45 a month, carries a larger number of networks, while Orange seems to have spent its lineup dollars on ESPN and ESPN 2. But at $40 monthly, Sling Orange is the cheapest way to get those two sports outlets.</p><p> After picking a plan, you can choose from a stable of add-on packages, with monthly prices ranging from $6 to $11. These include blocks of sports or lifestyle channels, kid-friendly fare, the Discovery+ bundle and a news package. There are 46 individual premium offerings, including Showtime, Starz, MGM+, Shudder and Acorn, which go for between $2 and $10 per month. Sling has pay-per-view movies, too.</p><p> As far as local coverage, Sling Blue grants access to ABC, Fox and NBC local affiliates in about 20 of the larger US markets including Los Angeles, Seattle, Dallas, NYC, Miami and DC. ABC coverage began in March 2023, but unfortunately, that raised the price of Sling Blue in supported markets from $40 to $45. For people not in those areas (or who opt for Orange) Sling is currently running a <a data-i13n="cpos:40;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Sling TV;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=34c77505-6db4-4664-9320-2c38b4122d5e&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Sling+TV&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiIzNGM3NzUwNS02ZGI0LTQ2NjQtOTMyMC0yYzM4YjQxMjJkNWUiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2xpbmcuY29tL3Byb2dyYW1taW5nL2xvY2FsLWNoYW5uZWxzIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI1MGViMzRkYi1jMGZjLTRiZmItYWI0MS0xY2JlOTdmYWZmZDgifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAe_a43827fNAzxdGbME6_g1Hxe1vYDxKcViw1EF1Ygsr&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sling.com%2Fprogramming%2Flocal-channels">promotion</a> for a free HD antenna to catch local stations.</p><p> Navigation is speedy and the interface is nicely organized, putting an emphasis on what you like to watch, with recommendations that are pretty accurate. The UI also makes the add-ons you&#39;ve chosen easy to find. In my tests, though, the app froze a number of times as I navigated. While most services froze once or twice, it happened enough times with Sling to frustrate me. I had to force quit or back out of the app and start over five or six times during the three weeks of testing. Compared to others, Sling&#39;s DVR allowance is on the stingy side, only giving you 50 hours of recordings, though they won&#39;t expire. You can pay for more DVR storage, but that will increase your overall costs.</p><p> I tried not to wander too far off-path during testing, but I feel it&#39;s my duty to inform you that Sling has an Elvis channel, a Bob Ross channel and ALF TV (yes, an entire station devoted to the &#39;80s sitcom starring a puppet). There&#39;s also a <a data-i13n="cpos:41;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5kb2d0di5jb20vIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI1MGViMzRkYi1jMGZjLTRiZmItYWI0MS0xY2JlOTdmYWZmZDgifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAfLLpz7B5Fdqmc2tN7mcDJLtJxgZvqFBK5LMTZRrKyJU&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dogtv.com%2F">Dog TV network</a> intended to be played for your dogs when you leave the house, which you can add to Sling or get as a standalone app.</p><ul><li><p> Base plan: Starting at $40/mo</p></li><li><p> Local channels: ABC, FOX, NBC in limited markets</p></li><li><p> Top cable channels: 22 or 29 of 36</p></li><li><p> DVR limits: 50 hours, no expiration</p></li><li><p> Profiles per account: 4</p></li><li><p> Simultaneous at-home streams: 1 or 3</p></li><li><p> Picture in picture mode: Yes</p></li></ul><h2> Best budget: Philo </h2><p><core-commerce id="9a1b66d1fc8b4bc9b2dd8a614d94dacd" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> At just $25 per month, <a data-i13n="cpos:42;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Philo;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=b250d7a0-0e4e-4332-bc87-bf6e669b0564&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Philo&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiJiMjUwZDdhMC0wZTRlLTQzMzItYmM4Ny1iZjZlNjY5YjA1NjQiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cucGhpbG8uY29tLyIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiNTBlYjM0ZGItYzBmYy00YmZiLWFiNDEtMWNiZTk3ZmFmZmQ4In0&amp;signature=AQAAAdsHmIjh3zVIRyP2fviwnS5u08Acnwz0UTQ3mtTL48ip&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.philo.com%2F">Philo</a> is one of the cheapest ways to get a cordless live TV experience. The biggest caveat is that you won&#39;t find any local stations or sports programming on it. If that&#39;s not an issue, Philo is great, with a clean, streamlined interface and generous DVR limits.</p><p> I&#39;m a fan of minimalist design, so I appreciated the way Philo presented its menus and guide. There are just four top navigation headings: Home, Guide, Saved and Search. And instead of the usual guide layout that stretches out or shortens a show&#39;s listing to represent its air time, Philo&#39;s guide features monospaced squares in chronological order with the duration of the program inside the square. Another nice touch is when you navigate to a square, it fills with a live video of the show or movie.</p><p> Philo doesn&#39;t limit the amount of programming you can DVR and lets you keep recordings for a full year, which is more than the nine months other providers allow. Like all live TV streamers, Philo won&#39;t let you fast forward VOD programming. If skipping commercials is important to you, I recommend taking advantage of that unlimited DVR policy and hitting “Save” on any show or movie you think you may want to watch, then fast forwarding it on playback (you can do this with all the services we tried).</p><p> As far as channels, Philo covers 23 of the top 36 cable networks, with notable exceptions including Fox News, CNN, ESPN and MSNBC. Anyone looking for great news coverage should look elsewhere anyway, but the lack of a few must-have entertainment outlets like Bravo and Freeform was a little disappointing.</p><ul><li><p> Base plan: $25/mo.</p></li><li><p> Local channels: No</p></li><li><p> Top cable channels: 23 of 36</p></li><li><p> DVR limits: Unlimited, one year expiration</p></li><li><p> Profiles per account: 10</p></li><li><p> Simultaneous streams: 3</p></li><li><p> Picture in picture mode: Yes (browser only)</p></li></ul> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/best-live-tv-streaming-service-133000410.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/best-live-tv-streaming-service-133000410.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 50eb34db-c0fc-4bfb-ab41-1cbe97faffd8</guid><dc:creator>艾米·斯科海姆</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Fri, 04 Aug 2023 15:00:49 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1691161250</ingested><modified> 2023-08-04T15:01:18+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Arts & Entertainment]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Amy Skorheim]]></category><media:content height="2880" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-03/e273db60-c41e-11ed-b0b9-11abb4ff0877" width="5120"><media:keywords> headline </media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="2880" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-03/e273db60-c41e-11ed-b0b9-11abb4ff0877" width="5120"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[gorodenkoff via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Black Couple Watches Professional Soccer Match on TV, Sitting on a Couch at Home in the Evening. Boyfriend and Girlfriend Football Fans Watch Sports. Back View Out of Focus Close Up Shot at Night.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Black Couple Watches Professional Soccer Match on TV, Sitting on a Couch at Home in the Evening. Boyfriend and Girlfriend Football Fans Watch Sports. Back View Out of Focus Close Up Shot at Night.]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Every Amazon division is working on generative AI projects]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>就像几乎所有其他主要科技公司一样，<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/tag/amazon/"><ins>亚马逊</ins></a>也非常关注生成人工智能。首席执行官安迪·贾西 (Andy Jassy) 在亚马逊最新的财报电话会议上指出，每个部门都有多个正在进行中的生成式人工智能项目。</p><p> “在亚马逊内部，我们的每个团队都致力于构建生成式人工智能应用程序，以重塑和增强客户体验，” <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://seekingalpha.com/article/4623663-amazon-com-inc-amzn-q2-2023-earnings-call-transcript"><ins>贾西说</ins></a>。 “但是，虽然我们将自己构建许多此类应用程序，但大多数应用程序将由其他公司构建，并且我们乐观地认为，其中最大数量将构建在<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/tag/aws/"><ins>[Amazon Web Services]</ins></a>上。请记住，人工智能的核心是数据.人们希望将生成式人工智能模型引入数据，而不是相反。”</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>为此，Jassy 表示，正如<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.theverge.com/2023/8/3/23819442/amazon-generative-ai-ceo"><em><ins>The Verge</ins></em></a>指出的那样，AWS 提供的<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazon-introduces-bedrock-a-cloud-service-for-ai-generated-text-and-images-204556563.html">服务</a>和基础设施可以帮助其客户<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazon-launches-an-accelerator-to-boost-generative-ai-startups-134746016.html"><ins>开发生成式 AI 应用程序</ins></a>。例如，AWS CodeWhisperer 系统旨在通过建议开发人员可以直接在代码编辑器中使用的代码片段<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/natural-language-programming-ais-are-taking-the-drudgery-out-of-coding-140015594.html"><ins>来加快开发人员的工作流程</ins></a>。</p><p>至于亚马逊计划在其面向消费者的产品和服务中使用生成式人工智能的方式，贾西略显羞涩，但强调了该技术对公司未来各个方面的重要性。</p><p>他说，这些项目“范围从帮助我们提高成本效益和简化各种业务运营方式的事物到我们提供的每项客户体验的绝对核心”。 “在我们的商店业务中也是如此，在我们的 AWS 业务中也是如此，在我们的广告业务中也是如此，在我们所有的设备中也是如此，你可以想象我们在<a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/tag/alexa/"><ins>Alexa</ins></a>方面所做的工作。这是真的“在我们的娱乐业务中，每一项业务都是如此。这将成为我们工作的核心。这对我们来说是一项重大投资和重点。”</p><p>当亚马逊于 9 月 20 日发布新设备时，我们可能会更多地了解亚马逊以消费者为中心的生成人工智能工作。该公司不可避免地会展示一系列由 Alexa 支持的产品。与此同时，考虑到<a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/watch-us-try-to-break-google-bard-and-bing-ai-153052165.html"><ins>谷歌和微软</ins></a>一直在开发新一代人工智能聊天机器人，看到亚马逊开始在其店面提供自己的聊天机器人也就不足为奇了。</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/every-amazon-division-is-working-on-generative-ai-projects-142836534.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/every-amazon-division-is-working-on-generative-ai-projects-142836534.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> ba91ccfc-c1d7-4090-9929-5b9eea7a0699</guid><dc:creator>克里斯·霍尔特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Fri, 04 Aug 2023 14:28:36 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1691158483</ingested><modified> 2023-08-04T14:14:48+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Kris Holt]]></category><media:content height="1837" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/2197a150-16ae-11ee-adde-69ed169b59bc" width="2969"><media:keywords> headline </media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1837" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/2197a150-16ae-11ee-adde-69ed169b59bc" width="2969"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ASSOCIATED PRESS]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[The Amazon logo is photographed at the Vivatech show in Paris, Thursday, June 15, 2023. (AP Photo/Michel Euler)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[France Vivatech Show]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA['Quake II' remaster might debut at QuakeCon next week]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/quakecon-2021-dates-bethesda-microsoft-xbox-164216413.html">QuakeCon</a>将于 8 月 10 日恢复现场活动，id Software 可能会重新发布版本以纪念这一时刻。历史上可靠的泄密者 Bil​​lbil-kun <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.dealabs.com/magazine/quake-ii-edition-amelioree-date-dannonce-officielle-et-plateformes-de-sortie-on-vous-revele-en-exclu-ce-que-lon-sait-concernant-le-retour-du-fps-26529">声称</a>id 将在下周 QuakeCon 开幕时推出<em>《雷神之锤 II》</em>的重制版。目前尚不清楚升级的详细信息，但经典续作将登陆 PC、PS4、PS5、Xbox One、Xbox Series X/S 和 Switch。该游戏将在发布时通过微软的 Game Pass 提供。</p><p> 2021 年推出的<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/quake-remaster-xbox-playstation-pc-switch-184030154.html"><em>Quake</em>增强版</a>可能会提供一些关于预期结果的线索。该重制版增加了对高达 4K 的宽屏分辨率的支持、新的角色模型以及升级的视觉效果，例如动态照明、景深和抗锯齿。此次更新还捆绑了所有官方扩展包，同时添加了由<em>《德军总部：新秩序》</em>开发商 MachineGames 创建的新战役。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>如果传言准确的话，这将与<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2019-11-26-quake-ii-rtx-1-2-updates-ray-tracing.html"><em>Quake II RTX</em></a>不同。 2019 年的调整旨在展示 NVIDIA 具有光线追踪照明和改进纹理的新型计算机 GPU，但不包括真正的新内容或与硬件无关的视觉改进。</p><p> <em>《雷神之锤 II》</em>最初于 1997 年发布，与前作相比，代表了技术和游戏玩法的重大进步。它引入了半开放的世界、基于目标的游戏玩法以及彩色灯光等视觉效果升级。第一个版本主要侧重于单人游戏模式（甚至在单人地图上进行在线竞争游戏），但由于更新和第三方升级（例如 ThreeWave 的 Capture the），它很快成为多人游戏的首选游戏。旗帜。</p><p>鉴于<em>《雷神之锤 II 重制版》</em>游戏已于 6 月通过了韩国游戏评级机构的认证，因此介绍这一内容并不令人意外。 Billbil-kun 还看到了北美 (ESRB) 和欧洲 (PEGI) 评级的文件。就目前情况而言，id、贝塞斯达和微软有动力继续制作《雷神之锤》重制版——他们让第一人称射击游戏成为众人瞩目的焦点，并使其可以在现代平台上玩，而无需诉诸非官方的修改和移植。</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/quake-ii-remaster-might-debut-at-quakecon-next-week-141123462.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/quake-ii-remaster-might-debut-at-quakecon-next-week-141123462.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 31166b9d-3f38-4a45-8145-b105a827d97d</guid><dc:creator> Jon Fingas</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher> Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Fri, 04 Aug 2023 14:11:23 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1691158285</ingested><modified> 2023-08-04T14:11:29+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Information Technology]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Jon Fingas]]></category><media:content height="1067" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2020-12/6c28c520-3eeb-11eb-ae37-d45509f00eba" width="1600"><media:keywords> headline </media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1067" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2020-12/6c28c520-3eeb-11eb-ae37-d45509f00eba" width="1600"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Lightspeed Studios/NVIDIA/id Software]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA['Quake II RTX' with ray tracing]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA['Quake II RTX' with ray tracing]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The best budget wireless earbuds for 2023]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>虽然绝对<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-wireless-earbuds-120058222.html">最好的真无线耳机的</a>价格往往在 150 至 300 美元之间，但市场已经成熟到无需花费三位数就能获得<em>足够好的</em>东西的程度。是的，您仍然会在特价箱中发现很多垃圾，但随着时间的推移，我们看到越来越多的耳机提供令人愉悦的音质、稳定的电池寿命和广泛的功能集，而不会给您的钱包带来沉重负担。为了帮助那些预算有限的人，我们研究并测试了一系列价格不到 100 美元的真无线耳机。这些是我们发现提供最佳价值的。</p><h2>最适合大多数人：Anker Soundcore Space A40 </h2><p><core-commerce id="5a01f240b4a5404d89ddee47e860ab45" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9zb3VuZGNvcmUtQWRhcHRpdmUtQ2FuY2VsbGluZy1Db21mb3J0YWJsZS1DdXN0b21pemF0aW9uL2RwL0IwQjFMVkM1Vlo_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tMW15LTIwIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiJiZjdiNjdmOC1lNDIxLTQ0NTAtOTZkYi1kOWNkYzE3MjhjN2EifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAd2bpndlMjVo9WZuMuDJnqRWTB8NdLYe6NZQSoJTWAk-&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fsoundcore-Adaptive-Cancelling-Comfortable-Customization%2Fdp%2FB0B1LVC5VZ" data-demonetize-referrer="https://www.amazon.com/soundcore-Adaptive-Cancelling-Comfortable-Customization/dp/B0B1LVC5VZ?th=1" class="rapid-with-clickid">Anker Soundcore Space A40 的</a>售价通常为 80 美元，但其性能和功能与价格两倍的耳机一样。它们的小圆形耳机重量轻且平衡均匀，因此对于大多数人来说一次佩戴几个小时应该不会感到痛苦。默认的声音配置文件已经足够好了：它很温暖，低音部有所凸起，高音部有所下降，这可能会削弱一些细节，但整体听起来很愉快。与许多更便宜的耳机不同，它并没有完全吹响低端耳机的声音。与许多现代配对一样，您可以使用 Soundcore 应用程序中的自定义 EQ 工具调整声音。使用这些耳机不会让 Space A40 听起来像市场上最好的无线耳塞一样好听，但它可以让它们的低音更深沉或高频更突出。该应用程序总体上易于使用，并且会将您所做的任何更改直接保存到耳机中。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> Space A40 的最佳功能是其主动降噪 (ANC) 功能，物超所值。它不会完全屏蔽高音调的声音，但它对于消除火车或喷气发动机的隆隆声非常有效。默认情况下，Anker 使用自适应 ANC 系统，该系统会根据您的周围环境自动调整强度，不过您也可以手动将其设置为强、中或弱级别。这对于耳朵敏感的人来说非常有用。还有一种透明模式，虽然不如<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/airpods-pro-review-second-generation-130048218.html">AirPods Pro</a>等高端产品那么好，但在紧要关头也能用。</p><p>您想要的现代耳机的大多数小细节也都在这里。 Space A40 可以同时连接到两台设备，并且您可以单独使用一只耳塞。电池续航时间稳定，每次充电可使用 8 小时左右，而随附的充电盒还可再续航 40 小时左右，并支持无线充电。 IPX4 防水等级没什么特别的，但仍然意味着耳机可以承受小雨和日常汗水。触摸控制方案可能会让人感觉有些忙碌，因为它允许您为不同的点击和长按分配最多六个不同的快捷方式，并有效地迫使您省略一两个功能，但它工作可靠。我们也没有遇到真正的连接问题。</p><p>唯一的主要缺点是麦克风质量以及摘下耳塞时无法自动暂停。前者不能很好地处理咝音，并且在特别嘈杂的区域可能会失去声音，因此这不是打电话的最佳选择，但它是可用的。</p><p>蓝牙：v5.2<br>主动降噪：是<br>透明模式：有<br>自定义均衡器：是<br>充电端口：USB-C<br>无线充电：有<br>防水等级：IPX4<br>多点连接：是（2 个设备）<br>自动暂停：无<br>电池寿命（额定）： 10 小时，带外壳 50 小时<br>快速充电（额定）：10 分钟 = 4 小时<br>编解码器：SBC、AAC、LDAC<br>保修期：18个月</p><h2>亚军：EarFun Air Pro 3 </h2><p><core-commerce id="592cd8376e734dd38c48d82bf6cf2f07" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p>如果你看到它们在打折，或者如果你更喜欢 AirPods 风格的“杆”设计，售价 80 美元的<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAWtxbryUICRZeUGXq-mBIgWJlonDfAi9Ek1SWkbh6dIy&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FEarFun-Air-Pro-Cancelling-Multipoint%2Fdp%2FB0BNNMYSGQ" class="rapid-with-clickid">EarFun Air Pro 3</a>是 Space A40 的值得称赞的替代品。与 Space A40 一样，它们配备了 ANC、透明模式、相对稳定的贴合性、支持 Qi 无线充电的便携式外壳以及同时连接两个设备的能力。电池续航时间稍差一些，比八小时接近六七小时，但也还不错。它们的 IPX5 防水等级要好一些，内置麦克风也是如此。</p><p> Air Pro 3 听起来也不错。默认情况下，它们具有令人兴奋的 V 形 EQ 曲线，具有强烈的低音和明显的高音尖峰。有些人可能会喜欢这个，因为它给 EDM 和流行音乐带来良好的重击感，但其他人可能会觉得它很疲劳，而且它会让更高的频率听起来太尖锐。 Space A40 的声音并不完全平衡，但对于大多数人来说应该更舒服一点。不过，您仍然可以使用 EarFun 应用程序中的（不太灵活的）自定义 EQ 工具来控制和个性化声音。</p><p>同样，Air Pro 3 的主动降噪功能在大多数情况下都可用，但它比 Space A40 落后半步，而且不可定制。另外，虽然该设计通常适合长时间聆听，但它比我们的首选产品更笨重。从好的方面来说，触摸控制稍微更广泛，因为您可以三次点击每个耳塞来访问其他快捷方式。</p><p>蓝牙：v5.3<br>主动降噪：是<br>透明模式：有<br>自定义均衡器：是<br>充电端口：USB-C<br>无线充电：有<br>防水等级：IPX5<br>多点连接：是（2 个设备）<br>自动暂停：无<br>电池寿命（额定）：ANC 打开时为 9 小时，ANC 关闭时为 7 小时，带充电盒时为 45 小时<br>快速充电（额定）：10 分钟 = 2 小时<br>编解码器：SBC、AAC、LC3、aptX 自适应<br>保修期：18个月</p><h2>50 美元以下最佳：EarFun Free 2S </h2><p><core-commerce id="aa121d4c5c1047fdb4a68d20f767e7aa" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p>如果您不想花超过 50 美元购买一套真正的无线耳机，请考虑<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAS25Zog3F-70sXE6oggL1--8fVQaE1VRaAjpECs054S5&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FEarFun-Qualcomm%25C2%25AE-Bluetooth-SweatshieldTM-Waterproof%2Fdp%2FB0BRV5VNYM%2F" data-demonetize-referrer="https://www.amazon.com/EarFun-Qualcomm%C2%AE-Bluetooth-SweatshieldTM-Waterproof/dp/B0BRV5VNYM/?th=1" class="rapid-with-clickid">Earfun Free 2S</a> 。与 Air Pro 3 一样，它具有较大的低音响应和较小的高音起伏。它会错过中频的细节，并且长时间使用会让人感到疲劳，但与这个价格范围内的大多数配对相比，它是这种“有趣”声音特征的更丰富的例子。您也可以通过 EarFun 的应用程序调整声音，尽管可供选择的 EQ 预设仍然比 Soundcore Space A40 少。</p><p>耳机本身的形状很好，尺寸也不算太大；结合柔软的硅胶耳塞，大多数人长时间佩戴都会感到舒适。 IPX7 等级意味着它们也完全防水。有一套可靠的触摸控制装置，电池寿命约为七小时。附带的充电盒又增加了 30 个小时左右的续航时间，并且还支持无线充电。它不是我们用过的最小的盒子，但也没有大到无法放入口袋。</p><p>也就是说，一旦你跌入这个价格范围，你就会开始遇到更多“一分钱一分货”的情况。除了听起来不如我们的高价产品<em>那么</em>尖锐之外，Free 2S 还缺乏主动降噪、多设备连接、自动暂停和透明模式。尽管他们的麦克风质量在大多数情况下都不错，但它很容易受到风噪声的影响。</p><p>蓝牙：v5.2<br>主动降噪：无<br>透明模式：无<br>自定义均衡器：是<br>充电端口：USB-C<br>无线充电：有<br>防水等级：IPX7<br>多点连接：无<br>自动暂停：无<br>电池寿命（额定）：7 小时，带外壳 30 小时<br>快速充电（额定）：10 分钟 = 2 小时<br>编解码器：SBC、AAC、aptX<br>保修期：18个月</p><h2>最适合锻炼：Jabra Elite 3 </h2><p><core-commerce id="0f56bb5acdf44186b215b83a318f2ae5" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAdycKvvDFRUnuvpvjvGRrLJgfMBNtxuaZAeE-ytGxQwa&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fgp%2Fproduct%2FB09B45T59G%2Fref%3Dox_sc_act_title_1" data-demonetize-referrer="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B09B45T59G/ref=ox_sc_act_title_1?smid=ATVPDKIKX0DER&amp;psc=1" class="rapid-with-clickid">Jabra Elite 3</a>已有几年历史，但由于它们的售价经常在 60 至 70 美元之间，因此仍然值得一看。它们对于锻炼特别有用，因为其紧凑的设计对于大多数人来说应该是贴身而舒适的。此外，它们不需要任何笨重的机翼稳定器或耳挂。它们还具有 IP55 防水等级，足以承受大多数健身房锻炼。 （与大多数耳塞一样，您应该在锻炼之间对它们进行轻微的清洁。）此外，它们使用物理按钮而不是触摸控制。当您在旅途中时，即时的触觉反馈对于快速更改曲目或调节音量更为可靠。</p><p> Elite 3 的音质仍然比这个价格范围内的大多数耳机都要好。正如<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/jabra-elite-3-review-120031350.html">我们在评测中</a>所指出的，Elite 3 的特点对于大多数音乐来说都足够平衡，具有轻微但不过分的低音增强，给曲目带来良好的身体感。默认情况下，它听起来比 Space A40 和 Air Pro 都要好一些：高音比前者更有存在感，而低音比后者没有那么轰鸣。它也比 Free 2S 更重，所以如果你看到 Elite 3 的售价在 50 美元左右，那就值得入手。与我们的其他首选类似，您还可以通过 Jabra Sound+ 应用程序自定义 Elite 3 的 EQ。</p><p> Elite 3 的不足之处在于其他方面。没有主动降噪功能，没有无线充电，没有多点连接，也没有自动暂停功能。虽然有透明模式，但效果非常微弱，因此您最好完全取下耳机。不过，七个小时左右的电池续航时间很稳定，如果需要，您可以一次使用一个耳塞。通话质量也可以接受，尽管不是一个突出的功能。</p><p>您还可以考虑<a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/jabras-elite-4-earbuds-forgo-a-few-niceties-for-a-20-price-cut-130037814.html">3 月份推出的</a><a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9ncC9wcm9kdWN0L0IwQlRaVEZKUEo_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tMW15LTIwIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiJiZjdiNjdmOC1lNDIxLTQ0NTAtOTZkYi1kOWNkYzE3MjhjN2EifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAVqJFq75PNSeCB2nw_CfAr1b_77K9-kwd98I81yK-Kxa&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fgp%2Fproduct%2FB0BTZTFJPJ" class="rapid-with-clickid">Elite 4</a> <em>&nbsp;</em>并具有 ANC 和多点连接功能。不过，对于大多数精打细算的买家来说，Space A40 的售价为 100 美元。</p><p>蓝牙：v5.2<br>主动降噪：无<br>透明模式：有<br>自定义均衡器：是<br>充电端口：USB-C<br>无线充电：无<br>防水等级：IP55<br>多点连接：无<br>自动暂停：无<br>电池寿命（测试）：7 小时、28 小时（带充电盒）<br>快速充电（额定）：10 分钟 = 1 小时<br>编解码器：SBC、aptX<br>保修：2 年（含 Sound+ 应用程序注册）</p><h2>最适合开放式设计：Amazon Echo Buds (2023) </h2><p><core-commerce id="ce4ab957d2e448419238fbc892075b00" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p>到目前为止，我们选择的所有产品从技术上来说都是<em>耳机</em>，这意味着它们会延伸到您的耳道中。对于许多人来说，这本质上是不舒服的。不幸的是，体面且价格实惠的“耳塞”市场参差不齐，这种“耳塞”放置在耳甲上，而不是一直放在耳朵里。不过，如果你不愿意花钱买一<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMEJESEI5WThILz90YWc9Z2RndDBjLXAtby0xbXktMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6ImJmN2I2N2Y4LWU0MjEtNDQ1MC05NmRiLWQ5Y2RjMTcyOGM3YSJ9&amp;signature=AQAAASkog1htC-e9cG55SoLiVxi-AK_Kbg8izCWmvtBbMZdD&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0BDHB9Y8H%2F" class="rapid-with-clickid">对 AirPods</a> ，那么 50 美元的<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAYvFNWl1lB8gmP6f7h7v8ZxkXU2LJD7Q0PvRz0iI6UIE&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FAll-new-Echo-Buds-2023-Release-True-Wireless-Earbuds%2Fdp%2FB09JVG3TWX%2Fref%3Dcm_cr_arp_d_product_top" data-demonetize-referrer="https://www.amazon.com/All-new-Echo-Buds-2023-Release-True-Wireless-Earbuds/dp/B09JVG3TWX/ref=cm_cr_arp_d_product_top?ie=UTF8" class="rapid-with-clickid">亚马逊 Echo Buds</a>是一个值得妥协的选择。</p><p>这里的塑料耳机并不完全优质，但它们轻轻地放在耳朵里，感觉很坚固。它们比入耳式耳机更容易引入和泄漏噪音，但如果您更喜欢开放式耳塞，那么这是一个功能而不是缺陷。如果感觉不合适，您可以<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:12;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAUYJ-VONzfl01ifLYVwQ7Dq8w9ZdjvcVYde5kIhznHP_&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fgp%2Fhelp%2Fcustomer%2Fdisplay.html" data-demonetize-referrer="https://www.amazon.com/gp/help/customer/display.html?nodeId=T1Ko041M2RpxQO3Nij&amp;language=en_US" class="rapid-with-clickid">通过取下</a>预装的硅胶盖来减轻一点体积。 （不过，与大多数开放式耳塞一样，这里的舒适度取决于您的耳朵形状。）麦克风质量绰绰有余，圆形触摸面板为使用控件提供了充足的空间，这些控件是可定制的且始终响应。电池寿命就在身边<em>&nbsp;</em>五个小时，虽然中等，但对于廉价耳机来说并不算不合时宜。 <em>&nbsp;</em>这款可放入口袋的保护壳可充满约 3 次电量，但值得注意的是，亚马逊不提供 USB-C 充电线。 IPX2 防水等级较差意味着您也应该避免去健身房。</p><p>虽然<a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazon-echo-buds-2023-review-50-goes-a-long-way-170007670.html">Echo Buds</a>开箱即用，音质很好，但我会使用 Alexa 应用程序中的 EQ 滑块将高音调低一两下。默认情况下，高音有点过于急躁。也就是说，这种强调给人声、铙钹和弦乐等东西带来了很好的清脆感，并且有足够的分离度来防止复杂的音轨听起来完全混乱。这里的配置文件不像<a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apple-airpods-review-2021-160026883.html">最新的 AirPods 那样</a>浓郁，也没有开放式耳塞能提供真正的低音，但至少有一些嘻哈和 EDM 的隆隆声。</p><p>与许多廉价耳塞不同，Echo Buds 支持自动暂停和多点连接。我经常不得不手动暂停一台设备上的播放，然后才能切换到另一台设备，但以这个价格拥有该功能非常棒。毫不奇怪，它们还内置了 Alexa，您可以免提访问它。您可以通过 Alexa 应用程序管理 Echo Buds，该应用程序比专用音频应用程序要混乱得多，但包括丢失设备跟踪器和电话呼叫侧音控制等附加功能。如果您不想与 Alexa 发生任何关系，它还可以让您关闭麦克风和唤醒词支持。</p><p>蓝牙：v5.2<br>主动降噪：无<br>透明模式：无<br>自定义均衡器：是<br>充电端口：USB-C<br>无线充电：无<br>防水等级：IPX2<br>多点连接：是（2 个设备）<br>自动暂停：有<br>电池寿命（额定）：5 小时，唤醒词关闭时 6 小时，充电盒时 20 小时<br>快速充电：15 分钟 = 2 小时<br>编解码器：SBC、AAC、aptX<br>保修期：1年</p><h2>荣誉奖</h2><h3>JLab Go Air Pop</h3><p>如果您只想花尽可能少的钱买到一副功能强大的无线耳机，请考虑一下<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:15;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAQtJBdz1uSWpBazTKgvZdpP6vnrfGYOOhF6G8WsybjxY&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FJLab-Wireless-Bluetooth-Resistance-Connection%2Fdp%2FB09HN594TL" class="rapid-with-clickid">JLab Go Air Pop</a> 。只需 25 美元，它们就拥有轻巧的设计、良好的隔离性能、8 至 9 小时的电池续航时间、IPX4 防水性能以及一整套实际可用的触摸控制功能。 JLab 甚至可以让您在耳机本身的三个 EQ 预设之间进行切换。如果你能负担得起的话，仍然值得升级到 EarFun Free 2S，因为相比之下，Go Air Pop 听起来更洪亮，而且高音和中高频不太清晰。也没有应用程序支持。但对于 25 美元，预计会有这样的权衡。 </p><p><core-commerce id="b4b171f99681475bb023a543494a3f2f" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><h3> QCY T20 AilyPods</h3><p>如果您想要最便宜的开放式耳机，请购买<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:16;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAUVXVhnbEP-0ExHYDl5bNySRnpUiqHKIz3OCaktuoAbA&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FQCY-T20-Bluetooth-Microphone-Headphone%2Fdp%2FB0B3LVS79G" class="rapid-with-clickid">QCY T20 AilyPods</a> 。它们毫不掩饰地抄袭了一个相对默默无闻的中国品牌的第三代 AirPods，但它们的售价为 33 美元，而且其令人愉悦的流畅声音可以说比开箱即用的 Echo Buds 更好。它们还具有更高的 IPX4 防水等级。然而，没有自动暂停或多点功能，而且它们的触摸控制几乎无法使用。 Echo Buds 的声音也更容易整理，因为 QCY 应用程序中的少数 EQ 预设实际上让事情变得更糟。 </p><p><core-commerce id="f56f65d0bf4041b5b6dff00e643138a5" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><h3>没有什么耳棒</h3><p><a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;cpos:17;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3VzLm5vdGhpbmcudGVjaC9wcm9kdWN0cy9lYXItc3RpY2siLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6ImJmN2I2N2Y4LWU0MjEtNDQ1MC05NmRiLWQ5Y2RjMTcyOGM3YSJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAX2F_vEtWiwIs9f5IDjpig3GYP9Y8WIRUpV4WEyWSACD&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fus.nothing.tech%2Fproducts%2Fear-stick" class="rapid-with-clickid">Nothing Ear Stick</a>采用<a data-i13n="cpos:18;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/nothing-ear-stick-hands-on-impressions-090050085.html">时尚的透明设计</a>，外壳看起来像一个大而透明的口红管。要使用耳塞，您只需扭转外壳即可，这总是很有趣。耳机感觉坚固且抛光，并具有围绕 AirPods 式柄挤压构建的灵敏控制。音频质量也不错，尽管默认情况下高音有点吵闹。主要问题是这些是未密封的耳机，售价 99 美元。这仍然低于我们的“预算”阈值，但对于一款用更少的软件技巧来弥补这种设计固有的声音牺牲的AirPods来说，它有点太接近AirPods的范围了。如果您注重美观并且<em>必须</em>拥有开放式耳塞，那么耳棒是一个很好的选择。大多数其他人都更喜欢 Space A40。 </p><p><core-commerce id="c376bb1e18344e5ea1c61d612294e836" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p