TA[Will AI revolutionize professional soccer recruitment?]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> Skeptics raised their eyebrows when Major League Soccer (MLS) <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/major-league-soccer-and-ai-io-announce-partnership-to-provide-all-players-with-a">announced plans</a> to deploy AI-powered tools in its recruiting program starting at the tail end of this year.美国职业足球大联盟将与总部位于伦敦的初创公司<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.ai.io/">ai.io</a>及其“ <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.ai.io/players">aiScout”</a>应用程序合作，帮助联盟在世界各地发现业余球员。此次史无前例的合作，是美国职业足球大联盟（MLS）首次在其此前严密的招聘计划中使用人工智能，让许多足球爱好者和人工智能粉丝不得不思考一个问题：人工智能终于进入了职业足球行业的主流吗？</p><p> There&#39;s no doubt that professional sports have been primed for the potential impact of artificial intelligence.创新有可能从管理和粉丝的角度改变我们消费和分析游戏的方式。特别是对于足球来说，有现场比赛分析、比赛结果建模、球跟踪、球员招募，甚至伤病预测的机会——机会似乎是无穷无尽的。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>西北大学凯洛格管理学院教授乔尔·夏皮罗 (Joel Shapiro) 表示：“我认为，我们正处于极其复杂地使用人工智能和高级分析来理解和预测人类行为的开始。”在这股浪潮中， <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://iris.unive.it/retrieve/8121e0e6-8ccb-4f2c-bfbf-ac502b0b8a65/Balzano-Bortoluzzi-2023-IPEJM.pdf">一些专家认为人工智能对职业足球行业的颠覆是及时的。</a>众所周知，足球是世界上最常见的运动。<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://guides.loc.gov/sports-industry/soccer">据美国国会图书馆称，</a>国际足联目前在全球拥有 2.4 亿注册球员和数十亿球迷，由 205 个会员协会和超过 30 万个俱乐部组成。 64场比赛刚开始几天， <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.fifa.com/tournaments/womens/womensworldcup/australia-new-zealand2023/media-releases/fifa-womens-world-cup-2023-tm-breaks-new-records">国际足联官员就表示</a>，澳大利亚和新西兰女足世界杯的观众人数已经打破了纪录。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/232aca90-2fbf-11ee-b7fb-08d8dd2d47e8" style="height:2296px;width:3476px;" alt="澳大利亚惠灵顿 - 7 月 27 日：7 月 27 日在惠灵顿地区体育场举行的国际足联澳大利亚和新西兰女足世界杯 2023 年 E 组美国队和荷兰队比赛期间，球员袖子上印有国际足联澳大利亚和新西兰女足世界杯官方徽章。 ，2023 年在新西兰惠灵顿。 （乔·普赖尔/Visionhaus 拍摄，盖蒂图片社拍摄）" data-uuid="f7b59a04-da84-3f41-b793-985e2abf2010"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Visionhaus 来自 Getty Images</div></figure><p>对更多球员和更多人才登上大舞台的需求使得<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.sportsrecruitingusa.com/">美国体育招募</a>(SRUSA) 等大学招生组织变得忙碌起来。 &quot;We&#39;ve got staff all over the world, predominantly in the US …everyone is always looking for players,&quot; said Chris Cousins, the founder and head of operations at SRUSA. Cousins 表示，他个人对人工智能对公司的潜在影响感到兴奋，事实上，他并没有因为实施影响 SRUSA 盈利的预测分析而受到威胁。</p><p> &quot;It probably will replace scouts,&quot; he added, but at the same time, he said he believes the deployment of AI will make things more efficient. “这将从根本上简化资源……这将为组织节省资金。” Cousins said that SRUSA has already started dabbling with AI, even if only in a modest way.它与一家名为<a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.veo.co/">Veo</a>的公司合作，部署无人机跟踪球员并收集视频供球探稍后分析。</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.ncsasports.org/">NCSA 大学招聘</a>男子足球高级招聘教练路易斯·科特尔 (Luis Cortell) 的看法不那么乐观，但仍然相信人工智能可以成为一项资产。 “Right now, soccer involves more of a feel for the player, and an understanding of the game, and there aren&#39;t any success metrics for college performance,&quot; he said. &quot;While AI won&#39;t fully fill that gap, there is an opportunity to help provide additional context.” </p><div id="d7204d05e3d54297995044291755347c"><blockquote class="instagram-media" data-instgrm-captioned data-instgrm-permalink="https://www.instagram.com/p/CB8aVstl5Fy/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading" data-instgrm-version="14" style="background:#FFF;border:0;margin:1px;max-width:540px;min-width:326px;padding:0;width:99.375%;"><div style="padding:16px;"><div style="display:flex;"><div style="background-color:#F4F4F4;height:40px;margin-right:14px;width:40px;"></div><div style="display:flex;"><div style="background-color:#F4F4F4;height:14px;margin-bottom:6px;width:100px;"></div><div style="background-color:#F4F4F4;height:14px;width:60px;"></div></div></div><div style="padding:19% 0;"></div><div style="display:block;height:50px;margin:0 auto 12px;width:50px;"></div><div style="padding-top:8px;"><div style="color:#3897f0;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;">在 Instagram 上查看这篇文章</div></div><div style="padding:12.5% 0;"></div><div style="display:flex;margin-bottom:14px;"><div><div style="background-color:#F4F4F4;height:12.5px;width:12.5px;"></div><div style="background-color:#F4F4F4;height:12.5px;width:12.5px;margin-right:14px;margin-left:2px;"></div><div style="background-color:#F4F4F4;height:12.5px;width:12.5px;"></div></div><div style="margin-left:8px;"><div style="background-color:#F4F4F4;height:20px;width:20px;"></div><div style="width:0;height:0;border-top:2px solid transparent;border-left:6px solid #f4f4f4;border-bottom:2px solid transparent;"></div></div><div style="margin-left:auto;"><div style="width:0px;border-top:8px solid #F4F4F4;border-right:8px solid transparent;"></div><div style="background-color:#F4F4F4;height:12px;width:16px;"></div><div style="width:0;height:0;border-top:8px solid #F4F4F4;border-left:8px solid transparent;"></div></div></div><div style="display:flex;margin-bottom:24px;"><div style="background-color:#F4F4F4;height:14px;margin-bottom:6px;width:224px;"></div><div style="background-color:#F4F4F4;height:14px;width:144px;"></div></div><p style="color:#c9c8cd;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;margin-bottom:0;margin-top:8px;overflow:hidden;padding:8px 0 7px;text-align:center;white-space:nowrap;"> <a href="https://www.instagram.com/p/CB8aVstl5Fy/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading" style="color:#c9c8cd;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;text-decoration:none;" target="_blank">aiScout (@aiscout_app) 分享的帖子</a></p></div></blockquote></div><p>与此同时，业内人士应该警惕将人工智能理想化为天赐之物。夏皮罗说：“人们期望人工智能是令人惊叹的，不会犯错误，或者即使犯了错误，也很少犯错误。”事实上，预测模型总会犯错误，但研究人员和投资者都希望确保该领域的人工智能创新能够比人类犯的错误“更少、成本更低”。</p><p>但最终，夏皮罗同意考辛斯的观点。他相信人工智能肯定会取代一些工资。 “它会取代球探吗？当然，”他说。然而，资源使用方式的最终决策者可能在一段时间内不会被人工智能取代。 Contrary to both perspectives, Richard Felton-Thomas, director of sports sciences and chief operating officer at ai.io, said the technology being developed and used by the MLS will not replace scouts. “[They] are super important to the mentality side, the personality side,&quot; he said. &quot;You&#39;ve still got to watch humans behave in their sporting arena to really talent ID them.” </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/69c112f0-315b-11ee-9dbb-2024c8989da0" style="height:4016px;width:6016px;" alt="麦考密克教授 Joel Shapiro 于 2020 年 2 月 25 日星期二在伊利诺伊州埃文斯顿教授分析课程。" data-uuid="5d3ac4f9-b1d1-3928-8598-6a06ab3f9c64"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">罗布·哈特摄</div></figure><p>When the <a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.ai.io/players">aiScout app</a> launches in the coming weeks and starts being deployed by the MLS later this year, players will be able to take videos of themselves performing specific drills.然后，这些内容将被上传并链接到<a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://www.ai.io/clubs">该应用程序的球探版本</a>，为特定团队工作的人才招聘人员可以根据他们选择的任何标准来发现球员。例如，球探可以寻找具有特定身高和踢球得分的守门员。将其视为社交媒体网站和搜索引擎的结合体。费尔顿-托马斯解释说，一旦做出选择，球探将决定是否应该在做出最终招募决定之前亲自观察球员。</p><p> Felton-Thomas 表示：“主要的人工智能实际上较少围绕评分进行，而更多地围绕视频处理和视频跟踪进行。” “运动以每秒 200 帧的速度进行，对吧？所以你不能只使用任何旧的跟踪模型。它追踪人类的速度不够快。”为分析视频内容而开发的人工智能算法可以将人类动作转化为构成玩家整体表现指标和能力的因素。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/9ec0c5c0-3220-11ee-bfb7-8ccc30d2c91b" style="height:3600px;width:5400px;" alt="新西兰惠灵顿 - 8 月 2 日：Seth Karunaratne（左）和 Bozhidar Kraev 于 2023 年 8 月 2 日在新西兰惠灵顿举行的 NZCIS 惠灵顿凤凰培训课程期间参加演习。 （哈根霍普金斯/盖蒂图片社拍摄）" data-uuid="b0ce3ed6-fbbf-31c9-b6ba-5dbcd6d3e85b"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">盖蒂图片社</div></figure><p>这些“绩效指标”可以包括招聘人员可以制定的传记数据、视频集锦和俱乐部特定基准。该公司在一份声明中表示，该平台的人工智能技术还能够对个人球员的“技术、运动、认知和心理测量能力”进行评分和比较。此外，人工智能可以根据可用俱乐部试验范围的基准评级生成反馈。 <a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1" href="https://www.fifa.com/technical/football-technology/innovation-programme">国际足联创新计划</a>是该协会测试和参与想要进入职业足球市场的新产品的实验机构，该计划报告称，与当前的黄金标准相比，ai.io 的人工智能工具显示出 97% 的准确率。</p><p> Beyond the practical applications of AI-powered tools to streamline some processes at SRUSA, Cousins said that he recognizes a lot of the talent recruitment process is “very opinion based&quot; and informed by potential bias. ai.io&#39;s talent recruitment app, because it is accessible to any player with a smartphone, broadens the MLS&#39; reach to disadvantaged populations.</p><p> The larger goal is for aiScout to potentially disrupt bias by continuing to play a huge role in who gets what opportunity, or at least in the pre-screening process. Now, a scout can make the call to see a player in real life based on objective data related to how a player can perform physically. “The clubs are starting to realize we can&#39;t just rely on someone&#39;s opinion,” Felton-Thomas said. Of course, it&#39;s not an end-all-be-all for bias, considering preferential humans are the ones coding the AI. There is no complete expunging of favoritism from the equation, but it is one step in the right direction.</p><p> aiScout 可以为来自偏远或弱势社区的球员打开大门，这些球员不一定有办法或机会在杯赛和锦标赛中被球探看到。 “在阿拉斯加或得克萨斯州或其他地方的某个超级遥远的人，无力为大俱乐部效力的人可能永远不会被合适的人看到，但有了这个平台，繁荣。他们将直接进入合适的人的眼睛”，考辛斯谈到 ai.io 的应用程序时说道。 </p><div id="c77409e430fa4e1eacc3e8fdbbc4ba07"><blockquote class="instagram-media" data-instgrm-captioned data-instgrm-permalink="https://www.instagram.com/p/CqJC2VltHql/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading" data-instgrm-version="14" style="background:#FFF;border:0;margin:1px;max-width:540px;min-width:326px;padding:0;width:99.375%;"><div style="padding:16px;"><div style="display:flex;"><div style="background-color:#F4F4F4;height:40px;margin-right:14px;width:40px;"></div><div style="display:flex;"><div style="background-color:#F4F4F4;height:14px;margin-bottom:6px;width:100px;"></div><div style="background-color:#F4F4F4;height:14px;width:60px;"></div></div></div><div style="padding:19% 0;"></div><div style="display:block;height:50px;margin:0 auto 12px;width:50px;"></div><div style="padding-top:8px;"><div style="color:#3897f0;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;">在 Instagram 上查看这篇文章</div></div><div style="padding:12.5% 0;"></div><div style="display:flex;margin-bottom:14px;"><div><div style="background-color:#F4F4F4;height:12.5px;width:12.5px;"></div><div style="background-color:#F4F4F4;height:12.5px;width:12.5px;margin-right:14px;margin-left:2px;"></div><div style="background-color:#F4F4F4;height:12.5px;width:12.5px;"></div></div><div style="margin-left:8px;"><div style="background-color:#F4F4F4;height:20px;width:20px;"></div><div style="width:0;height:0;border-top:2px solid transparent;border-left:6px solid #f4f4f4;border-bottom:2px solid transparent;"></div></div><div style="margin-left:auto;"><div style="width:0px;border-top:8px solid #F4F4F4;border-right:8px solid transparent;"></div><div style="background-color:#F4F4F4;height:12px;width:16px;"></div><div style="width:0;height:0;border-top:8px solid #F4F4F4;border-left:8px solid transparent;"></div></div></div><div style="display:flex;margin-bottom:24px;"><div style="background-color:#F4F4F4;height:14px;margin-bottom:6px;width:224px;"></div><div style="background-color:#F4F4F4;height:14px;width:144px;"></div></div><p style="color:#c9c8cd;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;margin-bottom:0;margin-top:8px;overflow:hidden;padding:8px 0 7px;text-align:center;white-space:nowrap;"> <a href="https://www.instagram.com/p/CqJC2VltHql/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading" style="color:#c9c8cd;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;text-decoration:none;" target="_blank">SRUSA 分享的帖子 - 🇺🇸 大学足球招募机构 (@sportsrecruitingusa)</a></p></div></blockquote></div><p> The <a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1" href="https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/mls-ai-io-partnership-how-technology-can-transform-soccer-scouting">MLS said in a statement</a> that ai.io&#39;s technology &quot;eliminates barriers like cost, geography and time commitment that traditionally limit the accessibility of talent discovery programs <a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1" href="https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/mls-ai-io-partnership-how-technology-can-transform-soccer-scouting">.</a> &quot; Felton-Thomas said it is more important to understand that ai.io will “democratize” the recruiting process for the MLS, ensuring physical skills are the most important metric when leagues and clubs are deciding where to invest their money. “我们希望做的是让俱乐部在决定签下谁和观看谁时有更高的信心。”通过实施人工智能驱动的应用程序，招聘时间预计也会缩短。</p><p> Silvia Ferrari, professor of mechanical and aerospace engineering at Cornell and ​​Associate Dean for cross-campus engineering research, who runs the university&#39;s &#39;Laboratory for Intelligent Systems and Controls&#39; couldn&#39;t agree more. AI has the potential to complement the expertise of recruiters while also helping, &quot;eliminate the bias that sometimes coaches might have for a particular player or a particular team,” Ferrari said.</p><p> In a similar vein, <a data-i13n="cpos:15;pos:1" href="https://news.cornell.edu/stories/2022/10/algorithms-predict-sports-teams-moves-80-accuracy">algorithms developed in Ferrari&#39;s lab can accurately predict the in-game actions of volleyball players with more than 80% accuracy.</a> Now the lab, which has been working on AI-powered predictive tools for the past three years, is collaborating with Cornell&#39;s Big Red men&#39;s ice hockey team to expand the project&#39;s applications <em>.</em> Ferrari and her team have trained the algorithm to extract data from videos of games and then use that to make predictions about game stats and player performance when shown a new set of data. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/5b851a20-2fc0-11ee-bd7f-02ccc38a637b" style="height:1053px;width:1069px;" alt="AI 模型中曲棍球运动员的照片系列" data-uuid="9bab1fe3-0078-3672-b16a-c3dd67f656ab"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> LISC实验室</div></figure><p>“我认为我们正在做的事情很容易适用于足球，”法拉利说。她说她的实验室不专注于足球的唯一原因是场地太大，她团队的摄像机无法总是提供易于分析的记录。她解释说，预测轨迹和跟踪球员也存在困难。然而，她表示，在曲棍球比赛中，挑战非常相似，但由于球员较少，场地较小，因此更容易应对变量。</p><p>虽然法拉利实验室的重点可能不是足球，但她相信，预测人工智能领域的研究使得“在体育领域开发人工智能更有希望，并且进展更快。”法拉利实验室开发的算法已经能够帮助球队分析不同的策略，从而帮助教练识别特定球员和对手的优势和劣势。“我认为我们正在取得非常快的进步，”法拉利说。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/5b858f50-2fc0-11ee-9df9-b7932b5d1520" style="height:916px;width:912px;" alt="AI 模型中曲棍球运动员的照片系列" data-uuid="cf9cd82d-9b9c-3679-9bcd-3f6933a7ecb9"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> LISC实验室</div></figure><p>法拉利计划尝试应用其实验室研究的下一个领域包括水肺潜水和跳伞。然而，法拉利承认存在一些技术障碍需要研究人员克服。 “当前的挑战是实时分析，”她说。许多挑战是基于这样一个事实：该技术只能根据历史数据进行预测。 Meaning, if there is a shortage of historical data, there is a limit to what the tech can predict. Felton-Thomas 表示，除了技术限制之外，在现实世界中实施人工智能成本高昂，而且如果没有正确的合作伙伴关系（例如与英特尔和 AWS 建立的合作伙伴关系），从财政上来说这是不可能的。</p><p> Felton-Thomas said ai.io anticipates “tens of millions of users over the next couple of years.”该公司将预期的增长归因于与合适的俱乐部的合作，例如英国的切尔西足球俱乐部和伯恩利足球俱乐部以及美国的美国职业足球大联盟。 And while aiScout was initially designed for soccer, the company claims that its core functionalities can be adapted for use in other sports. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/103a7480-3221-11ee-b7ff-827b3558df51" style="height:520px;width:1362px;" alt="康奈尔大学大红队的人工智能图像跟踪曲棍球运动员。" data-uuid="06ed06ad-b574-3f42-baba-3846558fbf0b"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> LISC实验室</div></figure><p>But despite ai.io&#39;s projections for growth and all the buzz around AI, the technology is still a long way from being widely trusted.从技术的角度来看，法拉利表示“还有很多工作要做”，而且很多改进的需要不仅仅是基于反馈算法历史数据的问题。预测模型需要足够智能，以适应当前不断变化的变量。最重要的是，公众对人工智能的怀疑在主流领域仍然很普遍，更不用说在足球领域了。</p><p> “如果这项运动发生了一点变化，如果球员的使用方式发生了一点变化，如果职业生涯中期运动员的治疗计划发生了变化，无论是什么，突然之间，我们的预测不太可能是好的， ”夏皮罗说。但他相信当前的模型将被证明是有价值且信息丰富的。至少有一段时间。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/will-ai-revolutionize-professional-soccer-recruitment-130045118.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[ht